<teaserText grammarName="coremedia-richtext-1.0"><div xmlns="http://www.coremedia.com/2003/richtext-1.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><p>A Southern specialty - this Upside Down Caramellized Apple Cake will entice you with flavours of cinnamon, caramel, brown sugar and butter.</p></div></teaserText>
<detailText grammarName="coremedia-richtext-1.0"><div xmlns="http://www.coremedia.com/2003/richtext-1.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><p class="p--heading-2">Introduction</p><p>A Southern specialty - this Upside Down Caramellized Apple Cake will entice you with flavours of cinnamon, caramel, brown sugar and butter. Best served with vanilla ice cream - and of course a cup of tea or coffee.</p><p>Why not try some strong dark-roast espresso?</p><p class="p--heading-2">Ingredients</p><ul><li>600g apples</li><li>220g sugar</li><li>4 eggs</li><li>125g butter</li><li>250g flour</li><li>1/2 package backing powder</li><li>2 teespoons oil</li><li>Rind of 1 lemon</li></ul><p class="p--heading-2">Preparation</p><ul><li>Mix quickly in the food processor the sugar and lemon rind</li><li>Add eggs and blend until it becomes a nice cream</li><li>Continue blending while slowly adding the oil</li><li>Blend until well mixedÂ </li><li>In a separate bowl sift the dry ingredients all together (flour, powder, salt)</li><li>Mix the dry ingredients slowly into the batter blending until it becomes a nice thick cream</li><li>Add grated apples and blend quickly into batter just to mix</li><li>Bake for 55 minutes until sticking a knife into center comes out clean</li></ul><p class="p--heading-2">Serving Suggestion</p><p>This very easy to make cake requires no fancy frosting or filling and is delicious for serving at breakfast, tea time or even as a birthday cake with a chocolate or fruit glaze covering.</p></div></detailText>
